      "content": "Swiss Associations offer a flexible and cost-effective legal wrapper for early-stage SNOs. They provide liability protection, separate legal personhood, and the ability to engage in commercial activities. Notably, Swiss Associations do not require registration, preserving privacy while maintaining compliance. Their reputation as part of Switzerland's crypto-friendly regulatory environment makes them ideal for DAOs transitioning into SNOs. They are typically used for the OCF and IPSPV, while the OH and RGH jurisdictions depend on payment flows.",
